### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@doctorId = 1

### 1. Criar novo médico
POST {{baseUrl}}/doctors
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1,
  "hospitalId": 1,
  "fullName": "Dr. João Silva",
  "cpf": "12345678901",
  "crm": "12345-SP",
  "specialty": "Cardiologia",
  "phone": "11987654321"
}

### 2. Listar todos os médicos
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors

### 3. Buscar médico por ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors/{{doctorId}}

### 4. Buscar médico inexistente (deve retornar 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors/999

### 5. Atualizar médico
PUT {{baseUrl}}/doctors/{{doctorId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1,
  "hospitalId": 1,
  "fullName": "Dr. João Silva Oliveira",
  "cpf": "12345678901",
  "crm": "12345-SP",
  "specialty": "Cardiologia Intervencionista",
  "phone": "11987654321"
}

### 6. Inativar médico (retorna erro - não implementado)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/doctors/{{doctorId}}/inactive

### 7. Criar médico com validação inválida (CPF curto)
POST {{baseUrl}}/doctors
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1,
  "hospitalId": 1,
  "fullName": "Dr. Maria Santos",
  "cpf": "123",
  "crm": "67890-RJ",
  "specialty": "Pediatria",
  "phone": "11999999999"
}

### 8. Criar médico com user inexistente (deve retornar 404)
POST {{baseUrl}}/doctors
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 999,
  "hospitalId": 1,
  "fullName": "Dr. Pedro Costa",
  "cpf": "98765432100",
  "crm": "11111-MG",
  "specialty": "Ortopedia",
  "phone": "11988888888"
}

### 9. Criar médico com hospital inexistente (deve retornar 404)
POST {{baseUrl}}/doctors
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1,
  "hospitalId": 999,
  "fullName": "Dra. Ana Paula",
  "cpf": "11111111111",
  "crm": "22222-RS",
  "specialty": "Dermatologia",
  "phone": "11977777777"
}
